  "texts": [
    "Mainstream psychology used it in the context of research related to human perception [80] elving into the role of curiosity and arousal and exploring how novelty can contribute to increased interest and attention.",
    "Besides, the novelty effect was related to learning and behavior.",
    "Hull's work on habit-family hierarchy and maze learning touches upon the role of novel stimuli in influencing learning and behavior [81].",
    "The novelty effect has also been associated with dispositional traits such as curiosity [82] and sensation-seeking [83].",
    "Regarding media psychology, the novelty effect has been observed in various technological advancements, influencing the perception and adoption of novel forms of media and entertainment [29, 84], affecting whether they are seen as a source of entertainment or perceived as a potential threat."
